That message is correct. For this test, assert the message too:

```java
@Test
void startAuthentication_shouldThrowBadRequest_whenAppIdMissing() throws Exception {
    mockMvc.perform(get("/auth/start"))
            .andExpect(status().isBadRequest())
            .andExpect(jsonPath("$.message")
                    .value("APP_ID header or appId query param is empty"));
}
```

Your `GlobalExceptionHandler` must include:

```java
@ExceptionHandler(IllegalArgumentException.class)
public ResponseEntity<Map<String, Object>> handleIllegalArgumentException(IllegalArgumentException ex) {
    return ResponseEntity.badRequest()
            .body(Map.of("message", ex.getMessage()));
}
```

If your handler also returns `error`, then add:

```java
.andExpect(jsonPath("$.error").value("BAD_REQUEST"))
```
